STATE
v.
Jeffrey Neal DUKE. No. 57A04. Supreme Court of North Carolina. June 30, 2005. Benjamin Dowling-Sendor, Assistant Appellate Defender, for Duke. William N. Farrell, Jr., Senior Deputy Attorney General, Michael K. Lands, District Attorney, Mikko Red Arrow, for State.

The following order has been entered on the motion filed on the 29th day of June 2005 by Attorney General for Extension of Time to File Brief:

"Motion Allowed. Attorney General (State of NC) shall have up to and including the 23rd day of August 2005 to file and serve his/her brief with this Court. By order of the Court in conference this the 30th day of June 2005."
